@page "/learn/options"
@layout MacroSutra.Web.Components.Layout.LandingLayout

<PageTitle>MacroSutra - Options Trading Guide</PageTitle>

<section class="landing-section">
    <div class="landing-container">
        <h1>Options Trading (V1)</h1>
        <p>MacroSutra supports single-leg options trading for buying calls, buying puts, selling covered calls, and selling cash-secured puts. Multi-leg strategies (spreads, iron condors) are planned for a future release.</p>

        <h2 id="supported" class="mt-4">Supported Brokerages</h2>
        <p>Options trading is available with brokerages that support options APIs:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Alpaca</strong> &mdash; Full options chain retrieval and order placement.</li>
            <li><strong>Tastytrade</strong> &mdash; Options-native broker with full chain and order support.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Other brokerages will show "Options not supported" and cannot be used for options orders. The Options page automatically filters to show only options-capable accounts.</p>

        <h2 id="chain" class="mt-4">Loading an Options Chain</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Trading &rarr; Options</strong> in the sidebar.</li>
            <li>Enter an underlying symbol (e.g., <strong>AAPL</strong>).</li>
            <li>Select a brokerage account from the dropdown (only options-supporting accounts are shown).</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Load Chain</strong>. The chain loads with available expirations.</li>
            <li>Select an expiration date from the dropdown. The chain displays calls on the left and puts on the right, with strike prices, bid/ask, volume, and open interest.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="placing" class="mt-4">Placing an Options Order</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Click a row in the calls or puts table to select a contract.</li>
            <li>Choose an action: <strong>Buy Call</strong>, <strong>Buy Put</strong>, <strong>Sell Call</strong>, or <strong>Sell Put</strong>.</li>
            <li>Enter the number of <strong>contracts</strong> (each contract represents 100 shares).</li>
            <li>Optionally enter a <strong>limit price</strong>. Leave blank for a market order.</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Place Order</strong>.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 id="tracking" class="mt-4">Tracking Options Trades</h2>
        <p>Options trades appear on the standard Trades page alongside equity trades. They are identified by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>A contract symbol (e.g., <code>AAPL240620C200</code>).</li>
            <li>The order type showing the specific action (BuyCall, BuyPut, SellCall, SellPut).</li>
            <li>An <strong>Options</strong> chip badge on the trade row.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="data-model" class="mt-4">Options Data Model</h2>
        <p>Each options trade includes an <code>OptionDetails</code> object with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>ContractSymbol</strong> &mdash; The OCC-format symbol.</li>
            <li><strong>UnderlyingSymbol</strong> &mdash; The underlying stock (e.g., AAPL).</li>
            <li><strong>OptionType</strong> &mdash; Call or Put.</li>
            <li><strong>ExpirationDate</strong> &mdash; Contract expiration date.</li>
            <li><strong>StrikePrice</strong> &mdash; The strike price.</li>
            <li><strong>Contracts</strong> &mdash; Number of contracts.</li>
            <li><strong>Greeks</strong> (optional) &mdash; Delta, Gamma, Theta, Vega, and Implied Volatility snapshot.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="api" class="mt-4">SDK &amp; API</h2>
<pre><code>// Get options chain
var chain = await client.Portfolio.GetOptionsChainAsync(
    brokerageAccountId: "bra-123",
    underlyingSymbol: "AAPL");

// Place an options order
var trade = await client.Portfolio.PlaceOptionsOrderAsync(new OptionsOrderRequest
{
    BrokerageAccountId = "bra-123",
    Symbol = "AAPL240620C200",
    Side = "Buy",
    OrderType = "BuyCall",
    Quantity = 5,
    LimitPrice = 3.50m
});</code></pre>

        <h2 id="limitations" class="mt-4">V1 Limitations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Single-leg only</strong> &mdash; Multi-leg strategies (vertical spreads, iron condors, strangles) are not yet supported.</li>
            <li><strong>No automated options strategies</strong> &mdash; Options orders are manual only; they cannot be triggered by strategy conditions.</li>
            <li><strong>Chain data</strong> &mdash; Options chain completeness depends on the broker's API. Some fields (Greeks, last price) may not be available from all providers.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-4"><a href="/learn">&larr; Back to Learn</a></p>
    </div>
</section>
